<TITLE> Hajj-flights take off </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 12 (bdnews24.com)The first Biman Bangladesh Airlines hajj flight left Dhaka with 285 pilgrims on board, a top official said. Khan Mosharraf Hossain, deputy general manager (public relations) of Biman, told bdnews24.com that the first hajj flight left Dhaka at 6:55am Monday. The second hajj flight left for Jeddah at 6:27pm with 258 pilgrims. Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed inaugurated the 2007 hajj flight at Zia International Airport. According to Biman's information centre, Biman is operating the hajj flights deploying two of its own DC-10 aircraft and a Boeing 747 taken on lease. Biman will run 170 hajj flights this year in and out of Jeddah and back home until Jan 24, Biman officials said. The Hajj Agencies Association of Bangladesh (HAAB) said accommodation for the pilgrims has been mostly arranged by now and the rest will be finalised soon. bdnew
